description:
&lt;p&gt;Our Radiology Department in our Wolverhampton Hospital currently have an opportunity for a bank MRI Radiographer . Start your journey with us whilst we’ll support you to be your best.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As our bank MRI radiographer, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;manage the day to day running of the MRI list&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;be able to perform a comprehensive range of routine and complex examinations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;preferably be able to canulate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;be competent scanning on a Philips Ingenia (or similar Philips) system&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The person&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To succeed as a bank MRI Radiographer you will need:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to be HCPC registered&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a minimum of 2 years post graduate experience in MRI&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to be a confident communicator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to be professional, flexible and reliable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Holiday in line with the Working Time Directive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to our Pension Scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discounted gym membership at £15.00 a month that they need to set up directly with the club. Discount does not extend to partners and family members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary -&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; £14.35 - £21.50 per hour (Dependant on Experience)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date - 26/11/2020 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location - Wolverhampton&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type - Bank&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working on the bank means you are not contracted to a set number of hours per week, but instead work on an ad-hoc basis to suit the needs of the business and your availability.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
